My World of Bags, in partnership with the Mastercard Foundation announced the launch of Kafawa (which means 'establishment' in Hausa), a training initiative designed to bridge the skills gap in the leather and non-leather manufacturing industry. My World of Bags, the parent company of FemiHandbags, one of Africa's leading luxury accessory brands, is partnering with the Mastercard Foundation's Young Africa Works to upskill hundreds of Nigerian youths and connect them to work opportunities in the creative sector. Read on.  Find out more about Mastercard Foundation in Africa.